hington, the 1st president of the US; or adoption of the surname in 1 above, in most cases probably for the same reason.","History: George Washington (1732–99), 1st president of the US (1789–97), was born at Bridges Creek, VA. His great-grandfather had emigrated from Dillicar in Westmorland in 1658. George Washington was a slaveowner, but he became troubled with the institution of slavery. Shortly before his death he decided that his slaves have to be freed after the death of his wife. — With the passage of time, the surname Washington has come to be borne by more African Americans (around 90% of all bearers) than English-Americans. A prominent example was the educator Booker T. Washington (1856–1915), born a slave in VA, who adopted his surname from his stepfather, Washington Ferguson."],"variants":[{"name":"President","meanings":["African American: from the English vocabulary word <i>president</i>, probably adopted as a surname in honor of one of the early presidents of the US (compare   Washington   and   Jefferson  ) or simply because of the importance of the presidential function."]},{"name":"Washinton","meanings":["Altered form of English   Washington  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alianore Washington was born about 1384, in Durham, England, her father, Sir William Washington, was 27 and her mother, Margaret de Moreville, was 29. She had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with William Tempest Knt.. She died on 2 January 1451, in Yorkshire, England, at the age of 68."},"et":{"about 1384–2 January 1451":"umbes 1384–2. jaanuar 1451","1384–1451":"1384–1451","1373–1441":"1373–1441","1408–1452":"1408–1452","1410–1462":"1410–1462","1417–1443":"1417–1443","1358–1399":"1358–1399","1357–1451":"1357–1451","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1373":"1373","1384":"1384","about 1408":"umbes 1408","8 June 1441":"8. juuni 1441","about 1417":"umbes 1417","1358":"1358","1357":"1357","1399":"1399","from 4 January 1443 to 20 December 1443":"4. jaanuar 1443 kuni 20. detsember 1443","1443":"1443